metadata.display_title: Remove commented out build dependency on oldest-supported-numpy
metadata.head_commit.author.name: Ivan Vilata-i-Balaguer
metadata.head_commit.committer.name: Ivan Vilata-i-Balaguer
metadata.head_commit.message:
Remove commented out build dependency on oldest-supported-numpy

python-blosc2 >= 2.2.6 depends on a version of NumPy (>= 1.20.3) which is
above that which oldest-supported-numpy depends on (1.17.3) (at least for
Python >= 3.8).

metadata.head_commit.author.name: Ivan Vilata-i-Balaguer
metadata.head_commit.committer.name: Ivan Vilata-i-Balaguer
metadata.head_commit.message:
Drop support for Python 3.8

At least when building and testing via CI.  This allows us to depend again on
oldest-supported-numpy at build time for increased ABI compatibility with
NumPy.  The temporary dependency on plain NumPy was caused by an
incompatibility between oldest-supported-numpy and the newer required version
of Blosc2 which only happened with Python 3.8.
